  "en_snotes_asad": "An allusion to all who assert that only the followers of their own denomination shall partake of God's grace in the hereafter. In other words, \"God will confirm the truth of what was true [in their respective beliefs] and show the falseness of what was false [therein]\" (Muhammad Abduh in Manar I, 428). The Qur'an maintains throughout that there is a substantial element of truth in all faiths based on divine revelation, and that their subsequent divergencies are the result of \"wishful beliefs\" (2:111) and of a gradual corruption of the original teachings. (See also 22:67-69.)",
